{
  "texts": [
    "The process of WCET analysis involves an examination of possible execution paths, accounting for variables such as computational load, system states, and hardware configurations.",
    "The goal is to identify the worstcase scenario that would result in the longest execution time, thereby enabling system designers to guarantee that all tasks will meet their deadlines, even in the most demanding circumstances.",
    "WCET analysis varies by method: some use direct measurements on hardware or simulations [1], while others calculate times using hardware models [2,3,4].",
    "Modeling techniques also vary significantly.",
    "For example, some methods require programming as an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST), and use analytical formulas (e.g., [5,6])."
  ]
}